=== Important Art Objects ===
* Stone zuigaki fences, 2 locations - {{ill|lt=Shōan|Q1327427|WD=Q1327427|1=Shōan}} 2 ({{ill|lt=1300|Q5609|WD=Q5609|1=1300}}).

=== Festivals ===
* Annual festival (May 3)
:: Called the '''Ogi Festival'''. Because it often rains and the route after the mikoshi procession becomes like a muddy field, it is also called the '''Muddy Field Festival'''. It includes an old-style rite commemorating {{ill|lt=Minamoto no Mitsunaka|Q2531241|WD=Q2531241|1=Minamoto no Mitsunaka}}, second generation of the {{ill|lt=Seiwa Genji|Q2164991|WD=Q2164991|1=Seiwa Genji}} who moved to Ogi in the late {{ill|lt=Heian period|Q193292|WD=Q193292|1=Heian period}}, as well as {{ill|lt=yabusame|Q1886157|WD=Q1886157|1=Yabusame}} and processions of mikoshi from five shrines.

